{
  "stem": "1033.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And we were handed a bread, we were handed an overcoat with the back cut out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It was a grey overcoat, a civilian coat, but the entire back was a big square was cut out with the letters K Z sewn in on a thin piece of cloth, which overcoat, incidentally, I had for many, many months, almost, until I was liberated in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And we got on this train, and we ended up in a place called Kaufering.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "It was called [INAUDIBLE], Kaufering.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "It was close to-- close to Munich-- about 60 miles from Munich.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And again, we had to get undressed, And everybody got examined.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And lo and behold, four kids-- I was one of them-- they wanted to send us back.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "We were not working material.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And the German commandant intervened and said that he'll put us in the kitchen to peel potatoes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Imagine that.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And a fellow called [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Bill ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Gleed, ?] who incidentally lives in Toronto, and who I met and who has pictures of the camp because he went back and took pictures, and myself went into the SS kitchen.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And I was there about two months peeling potatoes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "This was mid-November, so I was there till early January.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I was given a number.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was [GERMAN], which is 116,288.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a Dachau number.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was registered as George Spiegel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Another thing I didn't tell you about Auschwitz-- an interesting thing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As soon as we got in there, we were handed [? postcards ?] that we've got jobs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was pre-stamped.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had to address.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We're doing well.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we had to send that back to our relatives.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my aunt Bertha, who's the only person of my six sisters or my brothers who survived, got this postcard and momentarily, her fears were allayed about her parents, the kids, myself.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "This is really an aside which I should've mentioned at the beginning.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Anyhow, in January, we were taken out of the kitchen because some Hungarian women marched from Hungary.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were now walking.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Arrived-- Jewish women-- and they were put into the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And within about a week, I was transferred to another camp called [INAUDIBLE], and that was in Landsberg, again, in the same district.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, that would have been impossible.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No language, no strength, no-- I find that practically inconceivable for anyone to escape from there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no life force.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was-- there was-- One thing I do remember in Auschwitz that the [INAUDIBLE] Rabbi's son, full of sores-- one of the sons, a tall young boy, covered with sores-- he wouldn't eat.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember him being taken away, put on one of the trucks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was in October of 1944.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because I know he was somebody because the other people deferred to him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was just a young boy, maybe a little older.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He must've been 16.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was 14.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Tall, but covered with sores, skin and bones.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, no one can knock the power of prayer.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It really does take a hold on people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it is-- I don't know that I am insecure about God-- I mean, the conventional God-- because I'm Jewish so I was born insecure, or whether it is something that goes beyond my inheritance.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This boy was very sure of God.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And even though I know that religious people say it's a matter of saving your life, you can eat non-kosher things.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He didn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I'm sure that he was gassed and burned.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In this [INAUDIBLE] in Landsberg, we worked in underground facilities.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We don't know what it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I had to carry pebbles in a wheelbarrow from one place to another.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I really didn't understand what I was doing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But there were civilian Germans in charge of us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And occasionally, some of them gave me a bit of extra soup.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I could feel that they were kindly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And there were others, especially younger ones, who insisted that we march in sync to work, and we brought back people who died from the job.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We pushed them back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we were counted out and we were counted in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And about-- the end of February, early March, I was sick.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I was put into what they call a [INAUDIBLE] camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And it was another place where we were living in huts covered with earth.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And there, because of my experience, I was put into the kitchen, but for a very short time because my friend [INAUDIBLE] was there from the village [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I stole potatoes for him in the-- I tied my pants and I put them in where my trousers were.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I got caught and I lost my job.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I understand that he had survived and he's in Israel somewhere.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
